{"lemma":"شاهِين","slug":"شاهِين","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21513"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%87%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%86"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Indian falcon, especially the peregrine falcon","examples":[{"text":"يستطيع الشاهين أن ينقضّ بسرعة خاطفة تبلغ 360 كلم/سا. والمعروف أن أسرع مخلوق على اليابسة هو الفهد الصيّاد، وفي الماء سمك الكوْسج، إذ تبلغ سرعة كل منهما 110 كلم/سا."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pointer, needle of a balance scale"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a surname, Shahin or Chahine"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Middle Persian [Book Pahlavi needed] (šhyn' /⁠šāhēn⁠/, “falcon”, literally “kingly, majestic”)."},"ipa":["/ʃaː.hiːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21513","headword_ar":"شَاهِينٌ","root":"$Ahyn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain well-known bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of those that prey;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, * TA;) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the birds called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suquwr","text_ar":"صُقُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqorN","text_ar":"صَقْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], as are also the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baA$aq","text_ar":"بَاشَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAziY","text_ar":"بَازِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zur~aq","text_ar":"زُرَّق"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuw^oyuw^","text_ar":"يُوْيُو"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AHát in “ the Book of Birds, ” TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b$q","text_ar":"بشق"},{"kind":"text","text":";) [said by Golius, on the authority of Dmr, to be the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white falcon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to this bird it is perhaps applied by some of the Arabs; but some of them, I believe most of them, and I believe also that they do so most properly, apply this appellation in the present day to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gerfalcon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is not wholly white; and some, to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falcon gentle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the word is [of Pers. origin,] not genuine Arabio; (TA;) it is an arabicized word: the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awaAhiynu","text_ar":"شَوَاهِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayaAhiynu","text_ar":"شَيَاهِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in its stead, formed by substituion [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"] for facilitating the pronunciation. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwd","text_ar":"عَمُود"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beam"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the balance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SanojapN","text_ar":"صَنْجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A balance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a steelyard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a weight of a balance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: so in the Expos. of the “ Muwatta. ” (MF, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]}}